folder: West End Avenue & 93rd Street (West), Manhattan, NY
text:
West End Avenue at N.E. corner of 93rd Street, showing part of the N.W. corner.
The apartment building shown on the N.E. corner was erected about 1920 or possibly a little earlier. The remodelled house on the N.W. corner is one of five houses which will be replaced in 1928 by a 15-story apartment building.
About 1922.

New York Sun Staff Photographer.
Gift of E. M. Jenks.

folder: West End Avenue & 93rd Street (West), Manhattan, NY
text:
670 West End Avenue at S.E. corner of 93rd Street, a new apartment building replacing the old houses 670-78 shown in the June 1925 picture of this block, as well as the last five houses on 93rd Street. The remaining houses in the middle of the block on 93rd Street are 252-58.
The negative of this picture was cut; accordingly the adjoining building on West End Avenue is not shown.
1928.
